\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid8336051 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You only lived a short time in the house where you were born - do you remember why the family made their move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, to have more bedrooms because we'd assorted family - boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 This house that you lived in the lo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14312260\charrsid11677679 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 gest at Stanacre place - can you tell me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14312260\charrsid11677679  how}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  many rooms there were in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 There was just a living room and two bedrooms and they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14312260\charrsid11677679 partitioned
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  off for the girls and the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 So your mum and dad were in the front room and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14312260\charrsid11677679 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  girls and boys were in the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, dad and mother's had to be portioned off too because to make room, you see, she -
 she had to split us up you see - best way she could because we - you know, owing to the - me mother split us this way that - as we were growing older she made the eldest boy sleep in their room with them portioned off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Do you remember where your father came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, Pateley Bridge. Yes, Yorkshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You told me he was a tanner didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 My - my husband. My dad was a coalman. Coalman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Was he always a coalman or did he have any other job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well he did - he - he had another j
ob because during the slump when the big strikes was on he had to take something else because his business - because there was no - there was nothing for him to do but take another job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What did he do when he wasn't a coalman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well he - practically got anything he could get you know to - he - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14312260\charrsid11677679 you}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  know, help out because - in those days I mean they could really go and - do anything sort of thing if it were a labouring jobs, he'd do a bit of joinery or - well - h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14312260\charrsid11677679 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 lping out anyway - labouring anyway 
he could get you see because - the - the big strike was on, the coal strike you know and - he - he - well, practically lost his business with it and he had to just turn to what he could turn to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 But he went back to coal eventually did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Then h
e - he got back, his father set him up again in business and helped him back again to - you know - start where he left off but - to start from scratch and - coal then in those days you could buy a bag of coal for one and eleven a bag. Best coal only two s
hillings and two and tuppence a bag and - I mean they could - you know - well, had to sell quite a lot to earn, you know, to pay for the coal and then go hawk it in the streets. It weren't like it is at the present day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They didn't deliver to certain people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, oh no, to - to take it round you see and sell it at - at - you know, just to make that bit of profit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 did he ever have any part time jobs as well at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, he just had the - he had a little - bit of - used to do a bit of joine
ring and - and - you know, he'd - mend carts and paint carts you know, for the - well, he used to do it like, you know, to eke out - to try and have a cew shillings more you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You lived near the centre of Bradford did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, not - town, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Can you tell me where your mother came from - was she a Yorkshire woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, she - I believe my mother was born in Bradford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did se have a job before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, she was always in the mill was me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did she have a job after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, munitions. My mother went on munitions when me father went to fight in the 1914-18 war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You were telling me earlier that she also went to work in between having her children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, well she was in the mill then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 When you were tiny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
When we were little me mother went into the mill and stayed at home when she had each child. You know, and then went back again when she was able to - you know - put them to mind for a few shillings she'd go back in to the mill would me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Grandma. Mother's mother looked after us. But we stayed - during the - the 1914-18 war with dad being in - a soldier, my mother was allowed us dinners and me mother paid fivepence a - a week for each child and you got a penn'orth of dinner a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What did you get - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes. We got a right dashed good dinner for a penny and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you get it at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14312260\charrsid11677679 No, were sent from Old Elms school to this school at the bot
tom of Ottley Road called - it's now the Bradford Gregory school - and were sent there, but you could only go there for a penn'roth of dinner if your father was a soldier and your mother had to send her ring papers you know in those days.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well they - each - each soldiers wife had a - had - had a paper and they were called ring papers and were stamped were these papers - you're to take them and you're to show the headmaster these papers of your mother's to say your father was serving 
- a serving soldier, and each child was allowed then a penn'orth of dinner a day - fivepence a week it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What kind of dinners were these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They were hot dinners. Each dif - each day was different dinners. You - you had soup and you'd pudding a
nd you'd - big piece of bread you know to - for soup and on a Friday it was always fish and peas and if you - and potatoes. And sometimes it were called fish pie - sort of all mixed together but you always finished with a little pudding - like what you se
e
 now that's called rice pudding - those rice puddings in tins, well we got that pudding during the war years, all those years ago. That's right, in tins but they came in big tins but it was the actual pudding that we're eating today because it tasted same
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Before your father went in the Army how did you have your meals then - while your mother was working?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Grandma used to make them - me mother used to send a few potatoes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14312260\charrsid11677679 round
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  or - and a bit of meat and my grandmother - with having a - family of
 boys, my mothers's brothers - four - she'd four brothers and my mother and three was bachelor brothers and they never did marry. Was only one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
