\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, but he liked - he liked }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3100269\charrsid11677679 horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 racing like, I can - once or twice remember him going but - not as a regular think because I don't think he'd the money to go away you see because times became bad with him because people - didn't pay their - their way in them days an
d I mean they - they used to least of all think that they hadn't a right to pay coal money but - well, that didn't do my father any good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What happened when he delivered the coal and had to go back to get paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 He had to go collect the payments 
at weekend and many a time why my father drank beer was he'd many a time to go in a public house to get his two and tuppence and he won in the end. Well by the time he'd got that he'd already }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 bought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  a drink and - and he were at the losing end. Well it didn
't take my father long to be in queer street and I mean he had a good mother and a good father, they helped him. Used - they helped him many a times to keep his head }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 above}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  water or else we should }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 been in a poor way. But they - the big strike didn't do my father any good because it - it - sell everything he had and - well, it - start right from rank bottom but again}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 t it - to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 helped}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 with his parents like and I mean I don't think they ever got it back 'cos I don't think he were ever in't position to p
ay them back. Mind you they were - never - sort of came and bawled him for or nattered for it - it was you know, just off and forgotten sort of thing. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Do you remember your dad having a bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh yes. On - on - on all the big horse race, yes, he - sixpence each way. Yes, I do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did your mother and father belong to a savings club - a boot club or sick club or a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Me mother had to have a - a - a man call and she'd - she used to pay him always the same. One and six a we
ek and - year in and year out, she used to pay this one and six and it were mostly to keep us in shoes but many a time that - you know - it didn't run to shoes - you know - so many pairs of shoes 'cos there were too many feet and we were only - she could 
- same as if she bought us each a new pair for Whitsuntide well - she hadn't paid up for them time as were shoeless again so we had to make best of a bad job 'til she were able to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You didn't wear clogs as they did in Lancashire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, no we never wore clogs in Bradford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Were they in a funeral club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No. No. I can't ever remember me mother and father ever being in a - anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Any Insurance - for burying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh insurance - oh yes, they paid insuran
ce. Yes. The - I think me mother paid about - you know - penny or tuppence each. I think - was - we got ours when me mother and father died. They - the penny policies. Yes, we each got our own. It was still - you know. Yes, I have - I have one that me mot
her paid - a penny - they were put in at birth you know and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Only her - only her own mother and her own brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Never any neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No. Well - me
 mother relied mostly on her own mother 'cos she'd a right good mother. And - were more - if ever we wanted anything or if ever she needed anything we always went to ask me grandma or me mother's brothers because - I tell you out of the four brothers ther
e was only one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  and he was the youngest. And they was able to give me mother a shilling or two but they always gave it her on quiet.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Because they were always frightened me dad going and having an drink with it if he knew. That - that 
- so they always gave me mother many a time - it'd only be same as a few shillings and many a time I've gone round and - to see me grandma and if her brothers has been in they've gone - is your dad in because if you' dad's in don't give your mother this a
nd - they'd send me mother a few shillings. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Then used to slip you a few coppers to spend?We
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well - it - it just depend - same as if you wanted anything right badly and you went to ask me - me mother's brothers they'd say, well go on - y
ou know - well see between us if we can buy it. But it never had to be a big lot in them days. And if you wanted to go anywhere - right badly - tey'd, you know, help you to go. And as if they were - they used to have little outings at school you know wher
e you could go on a trip and it'd only be like a - a few coppers or things like that that you could always rely on being able to go if me mother's brothers were about because they'd let you go, you see, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What would you do on these outings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well sometimes - in the - you know, they used to take you to - we mostly went to another park or something for a nature study or anything like that you know and it - it wouldn't be for a right lot if enjoyment but still you'd go on't bus and - you know, a
nd be able to buy a - a few sweets you know and things - it wore like half a day's trip to us because we never went to seaside as children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you ever go away on a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, never 'til we grew up, we were able to - save up for ourselves. My mother were never able to take us to seaside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you go at all on Bank Holiday - did you do anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, never able to go on - I never remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 ing to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 seaside}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 as a little girl - never once. I - mother never - were able to take you to seaside. Wish she could you know and that's what made my mother bitter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 That she couldn't take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 That she couldn't take us out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage - do you remember}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679  what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  happened when one of your younger brothers or sisters were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Yes, yes, me - it were mostly me grandma used to come round to see that she was all right, bring her a drop of gruel or a - or a - when she were in bed with her baby she used to - you know, I can always remem
ber her give - making her some toast and a pint of tea and making some gruel that she used to make me mother always stay in bed the length of time that the doctor or nurse made her stay in bed so as she were able to get up and look after her family.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Gruel was made with milk and oatmeal wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 That's right. Yes. Gran}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 ma used to provide it. Yes, I can remember seeing me grandma come round with jug with - gruel in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Do you remember any of the other children being born, your brothers or siste
rs at all? You told me you remembered during the war years when your brothers or sisters were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 queuing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  at the Maypole for me mother's little rations and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 I got home they said nurse had been with baby. And - I - I can remember it pl
ain as though it were yesterday. And what stands out most in my memory as a child is, when I went to those dinners at school as a child - as a - as a - you know, to the - you know, I told you I went because me father was a serving soldier and I had to go 
t
o these school dinners and we at school that were able to carry any of the little ones down had to carry them all the way to school and all the way back and on the way back from school there used to be a lady and gentleman had a shop in Hockley Road and t
h
ey had it for years and as we was coming up from dinners they were very kind people, they'd do without the bread that was rationed to give to the children that was going to these dinners. Because many a time the boys didn't really get what fed a boy you k
now, a growing boy, to have your penn'orth }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 dinner. And - and I often think as - as old as what I am now - little did them people think when they were giving slices of bread out to us passing as children that we were the children of the serving soldiers 
and our brothers that were walking at side of us were the next soldiers what was serving - going to serve in the 1914 war and - and they'd have passed on with me grandma and all them and that's - to me it's - it's - one - well - it's a memory that I -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 The 1930 war you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
That's - the - yes. Yes, they were the serving soldiers. And - all three brothers served in - in the war. All - all my three brothers and my mother's - everyone in the family - there was only one man back and me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  out o
f - all the family. Me mother's brothers served - all the four brothers served and - my - me father served and then - as our brothers, you know, came up - came up, they served. My three brothers went. And I've lived to see my two sons go. To - to do their
 
service. One went to Malaya and the other went to Germany. Yes. Yes. It isn't many that can hold many memories of that and I - and - I saw me own father march down Hockley Road to go serve and go overseas and I saw also me uncles go - down - march down Ho
c
kley Road and we were only - the old people of Bradford remember the - the trams - coming up for their men to recruit - they were all illuminated cars, there won't be so many folks remember them, asking for recruits. Yes, and there used to be band on top 
playing and all these tram cars were illuminated. And - and it was serve for Kitchener and things like that they used to be shouting over these - big phones that they had. Yes, I can remember it as plain as it were yesterday. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 When I think of those people ho
w many slices of bread that they gave away I thought only - as I was sitting I thought by jingo, as a child and I went to dinners and came home little did I think that my brothers were receiving a slice of bread from them would serve in the next war. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, and they - they were giving it because me father was serving in the 1914-18 war. Yes. So we've had our share of wars and - the lads serving if that's all to go by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Your parents had your granny living nearby - did you have any other relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Only aunties and uncles like - me mother's brothers like and grandma all lived in one big house and - me mother's sister lived very close by that only had the two children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you see much of them - did you visit each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh yes.
 They - they - they were a very close family and a clinging family you see. Although the - me auntie and - and her brother that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 they only each had two children, they always had plenty to spare for us like as regards clothes and things that they
'd done with because they always thought it was awful that me mother should have such a lot and - you know - and each of those they'd only two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did they ever say this to your mother though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes. And that really hurt my mother deep down because m
e mother were bitter this way - she thought in her own mind she were never wanted because she had the big family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Never wanted by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 She always felt that - that they didn't make as much fuss about her because she had the big family but - I th
ink me mother was wrong because I can never ever remember me grandparents ever refusing to help me mother or that but me mother were - sort of - I just can't really put it - I think me mother were - let's say - I don't think she were - bitter but she were
 a sad person, that she couldn't give what she wanted to give because she'd nothing to give with. Only - a good hard day's work And she gave that - she gave that although she were - had so many children. She served on munitions did my mother and 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Barry Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} munitions and so did me auntie. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 
And as I tell you, they served one week days and one week nights.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 So she had her baby and then as soon as she'd finished feeding it she was back to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Every - she was back to work. And my grandmother had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 So really she didn't get a lot of pleasure out of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 My mother never - my mother never knew what it was to go out and me mother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 knew what it was to get a lot of new clothes. And you see - when she used to see her sister she were always sort o
f better dressed and me mother used to feel sort of down - you know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  trodden}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 on sort of thing. But nearly everybody on our street and all bit families. Yes. They were the - it were eights, nines and tens and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 thirteen\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  and fourteens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 So there'd be a lot of poverty on the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
So there were lots - everybody was alike. But - me mother were a very, very clean person. Very clean person because what we - me mother used to wash every day and every night and work besides. Every day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did your parents have a lot of friends and where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
No, they didn't. Mother - only friends were mother's own neighbours that were in same boat as herself. And she was - and they helped one another - say that. You know, if - if one needed help -
 same as if one had a baby and you could help and you could take a bit of washing you'd do it and that's way they got on.
