\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 So you received your ideas from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 From - yes, me mother and father, yes. Anybody that's sort of drifted away from family life. Each one of
 us always seems to have that family life, you know, more or less like it was at home. Held together sort of thing and - mind after me mother and father died we broke away from one another, which you do break away but - if ever we needed we're there, and 
we meet occasionally because we're met -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Were friends ever invited to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh yes, we could have friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Your mother and father too - did they have friends to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well me mother and father had very few friends come to the
 house. If anybody came it were mostly to see me father about - business or talk business with him. But we were allowed to have our friends and if me mother had anything to spare she never turned them a drift - they'd always be able to stop for their tea 
but it were a bit less for us like but it were - we were allowed to have them just same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They were given something to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They were given something to eat, always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did they call in casually without an invitation or did they have to be invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Oh we could - we could have our friends and we could play with our own friends sort of thing. We'd each our own individual friends like apart from brothers and sisters. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or relations or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, they al - no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
It were - the - the neighbours that we had mostly they saw during the day, you know, there were no going out - me mother never left us. That was something me mother never bel
ieved in. Leaving you at night - no. Me mother never left us, she were always there were me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 People say that they used to make their own amusements in those days, what happened when you bought your friends in or neighbours came in?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well i
t were - it were - music - a bit of music and - I had an auntie and uncle that could sing and - they - they were real good singer and all and if ever they came round it used to be right grand, it used to be like a right little family gathering you know an
d
 it - it were right nice and - me uncle were a right - well, me uncle and auntie were two real good singers and - me mother's sister and her husband and they used to love to come round and they'd bring their two children and sometimes - they'd - you know 
- sometimes bring something to it, it just depended like if they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Bring their own supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Yes, and - or we'd buy - never buy you fish but they'd buy you a few chips - in those days you could get a penn'orth of chips you know and - get - you
 know - it'd be - same as if it were - holiday time I think was like that you know that they mostly used to come to visit sort of thing - visit me mother. But it were very rare that my mother visited them. Very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Many people divided society into d
ifferent social classes or groups in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh yes. You found people even in your own street that were very stand-offish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well - as I tell you, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 if}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 they'd only one child or two child they thought they were a cut above you sort of thing. Although they'd have very poor jobs and - they were - you could find that even - even when I were a child you could - you know - and you never got that friendliness 
w
ith people like that like you did where they had the bigger families and the most to do. You never found that same atmosphere where they all - say only one child or - you know. Oh yes, you - you did find, you know, that a lot. You even found it in our - y
ou know - when we were going to school that - people could be very, very stand-offish like you know, a certain }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 class}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 of folks could be very stand-offish, things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well - it'd just be like the working class sort of thing, you know, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well - as I tell you, they were all those with the big families that stuck together the most and they were - they were the happiest fa
milies. If that's what you mean. Yes. You - you even found that out with how me father ran his business. They're people that used to buy a bag of coal and say bring it best coal and they could ill afford to pay for it when you'd taken it because they thou
ght - you know - they were better than you, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Why do you think they thought this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well I - I just don't know, they were just that type of people you get them in all walks of life, you meet them even at this day that think they're that sl
ice of loaf better than you and they aren't when it boils down are they. They're no better of 'cos - each individual no matter how - how simple it is they all have to work for their living and they all have to hold their hand out for their wage no matter 
h
ow they get it do they. They have - they can have the best jobs going but they all have to do same as the humblest person - hold your hand out at weekend to draw what you've earnt haven't they. And it - I mean - to me it's all wrong when they think that a
bout - you know - they - that they're better. They're better off aren't they in a way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Can you remember being brought up to treat some people as different from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well I mean }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 some}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  - we never were brought up to treat any different but I mean
, they used to treat us different because they used to look down on you if you belonged a big family because - you weren't as well dressed as what they were even in them days you know, they'd always that, you know, even at school - they distinguished at s
chool if you belonged a big family, oh, you belonged so and so like they used to - you know - turn their noses up sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Were you ever taught to show respect to some people in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh yes, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you ever call anyone Sir or Master or Madam and who was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Oh no, it - no - the only - no, the only people I've done that more as I've grown older because I've worked for people that have been - held - held better }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 positions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  And I mean - I've - I've worked for all sorts of people. I've worked for doctors and nurses and people at Town Hall and - and mill owners. Even up to - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 That wasn't before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No. That wasn't before 1918. But - no, they were just the ordinary type of everyday person that we lived amongs
t and - and - sort of communicated with, you know, everyday I mean, we lived there so long amongst the same families as a matter of fact, year after year, year after year and watched - them grow up same as we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 In the district where you lived who w
as considered the most important people? And did you come in contact with them - why were they considered important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well it were only same as the business people - those that had - same as shops or - or things like that you know or - or - it were - 
it were no ordinary people same as ourselves - they were - you know - they were - well sort of more or less all alike you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Why do you think the business people were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well 'cos they were - they was - some of them were - sort of snobbish like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Who do you think the shopkeepers mixed with socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well I mean - there were very, very few that had a car in those days, you know, they were - they were right out of question if they'd a car or anything like th
at. No, I can't ever say that we - were saw - a big lot of anybody apart from the folks that we lived amongst you know, right - well, right from me being a girl up to being twenty-one we sort of - I saw everybody that I'd lived amongst grow up sort of thi
ng you know and in same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Who do you think the teachers mixed with or the clergy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well I don't really know the teachers where we went all - always sort of were on - you know - mixed with their own class of teaching.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What about the vicars at your mission, who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well they were - those that were with us always with the poor children - always was with the poor children and always doing things for the poor children. They ran things and did things every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What about the bosses at the mill, who do you think they mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh I've no idea. Only when they wanted you to do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They wouldn't mix with you unless they wanted you to do something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 That's all - Sometimes mill manager, it were a pound to speak to him but if he wanted anything he knew where to find you. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 You know, but - it - bosses didn't mix with you. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
No. In - in mill the bosses kept away - in fact, you never hardly saw any of the big men that ran the mill, it were mostly the overlook
ers and the - you know - things like that, we never saw anybody big like that belonged the mill. That you never hardly saw them come round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did you feel about the bossed in the mill - did you like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well we had a good boss - that we work
ed for because all the family had served him and he sort of respected us because he got a lot of good years out of us all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You think this was it do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, I do because he used to say when - when he saw another of the family going - by }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 jingo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 , he used to say to me mother - how many more have you Annie because it were more employment and we all worked at same mill. Yes, even me brother.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What sort of people do you think went to church and what type went to chapel - did you notice any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well I mean the - I can't say really a big lot because we never went to - we never went - to the - big - we had to go to our own church from school because it was a church school but for going there at Sundays we never attended there to see what -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You went to a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes. We never attended there because we always - I tell you, for years and years, up to growing up and working we went to this mission.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
No, round where we were they were mostly - mostly same people. They were all in same - same state as my own mother were in. They'd all big families and plenty to do and very little to - to
 live on - they'd to scrape through best way they could or - nearly all on our street, and they're all grown up and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 and about to be and they're all same as what we are - they're all the folks that we grew up with. We see them every day when we go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 Bradford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You do say one lot thought themselves superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Oh yes. There they'd only one - if they'd one child like as could dress 'em nicer well that were it - you see, they didn't used to have to bother with - them that had a lot of family because you weren't dressed same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you think of some people as rough and some as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 respectable}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well there were very - very few that - that caused any real trouble by - where I lived because they were all more or less same you - there were no roughnecks and there were no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 arguing}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  and shouting and aggressiveness you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you think of some other people as respectable though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh there were plenty - there were plenty nice families and good families - good living families that - you kno
w - were all sorts but they more or less had big families where - where I was brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you think there was a distinction between craftsmen and labourers then in families - do you think this made a distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well I - that could be becau
se I mean that happened when me mother's brothers. They were all - brought up - they were a bit - you know - above the - yes, and I mean, I do know that's right because - through the years I remembered being a girl, my mother's brothers hardly never mixed
 
with anybody. They were their own business people and their business is going today and I mean - they - well they - they'd very, very few friends had me mother's brothers because they never mixed with anybody - they lived very - you know - quite life did 
me mother's brothers like - me -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well they were friendly - me mother and father were very friendly, yes, very friendly towards everybody because folk were friendly with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Do you think your mother thought of herself as belonging to a certain social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
No, that - no, me mother were - what my mother felt was to herself and - and in her own home. She never were - you never heard my mother be bitter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  anybody that - 
if they'd have had - you know - everything in the world, me mother wouldn't have been bitter or jealous about 'em. Me mother lived in her own home in her own world. Yes, me mother made her own - you know - her own home, her own place and that were it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Before 1918 do you think it was possible to move from class or group to another - do you remember any-one who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh they - there'd be a few like but I don't remember much about them like the - well like - all I can remember more or less were livin
g in this same place all the time so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You don't remember anybody who went up in the world or anybody who went down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, not really but - they mostly - even now they - the younger end, they thought that - their mothers and fathers are }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3100269\charrsid11677679 dead}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  but t
hey're mostly - there's - oh lots and lots of them still living - you know - same as our family, that are all - and nice - have nice goings on even now that's come out of really noting, you know, nice good jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How do you think they came up then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well I think - I think they did it themselves, you know, the hard way - the hard work - they it theirself with good hard work you know because - even me own brother - he's - he - he came right from the bottom where he came out of the mill, he got a job 
and he - he came right through the G.P.O. to be right from a sorter and he - he went out on - on the rounds to get onto the - what they call counter in the big - you know - and he - it - he did it the hard way - got there the hard way, of his - off his ow
n bat sort of thing but he - now he's just had to retire owing to ill health and he's been in the Post Office years and years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 So you thought if they did move up it was through hard work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 It was - through their own hard work - their - their own s
elves, it wasn't with money because folk hadn't money to help them to be educated in those days. And I - mean you - you heard of very few going to secondary schools - very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Do you remember anyone being described as a real lady or a real gentleman then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Not round about by us love. No, I don't ever remember - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you ever see the landlord and what did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well he - he were there every week for his rent and if he didn't get it -
 there - there'd be a row but he'd come back like - he - he'd be there but I mean - that's something me mother always did, she used to say, if you pay for your shelter and you've a shelter over your head no matter what poverty have inside you can - abide 
by that as long as you've a shelter. And me mother always used to see that rent were paid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What did you feel about it as a child and what difference did it make t
o the family when your father was ill or out of work? Do you remember him being ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
I can't remember me father being ill much. No. And he was - yes - he - well he went doing all sorts of things but - he - he did manage to bring me mother a few shillings each time but - me mother always kept her independence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You never had to go to anybody for help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No. Only me mother's own people. Yes. And what's more, me mother - would earn a few shillings even if she died doing it. To keep
 her own independence and I mean that's how me mother come to work all through the years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did you feel about this as a child when you you're your mother struggled so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, I used to feel hurt because - you know - when - I - so other - I used
 to say to me mother many times - why is you're always to - to work mother and - and other folk - other kiddies mothers haven't to work? She says, no, may be they've a better going on than us, and she said, if I didn't work you wouldn't get the things tha
t - that you get now. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 
And she worked because she wanted to - try - but it were only a try because she couldn't do it because even with me mother's help couldn't provide for ten children to get the things that she needed for us and we had to go short many, many times.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 And it upset you did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well it did because - you nursed that bitterness you know, you used to think like when I get older and - I'll - I'll do better, but you didn't do any better really but - except that the jobs were a bit better and wages were a bit better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 And you didn't have so many children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
And you didn't have the big families and that - but you were no better because in fact - to us - mother did a job well done on the bit that they had and I mean they all deserved 
Victoria Cross in them days that struggled to bring a big family up on the bits that they had - coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You told me you were three when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, we all were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You told me it was a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes. We all went at three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What time in the morning did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Nine o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What time did you finish at lunch time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Then you worked in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 When you first started did you go afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No. We were
 - our school were allowed to go one week mornings and one week afternoons. And when you went mornings you'd to start same as - the mill started. You want half days at half past six - you'd to be set off and the mill'd start and you'd work until dinner ti
me, you'd come home and have your dinner and you'd go to school but some schools in other towns worked one day - a full day and next day to school but our school never did. We had to do a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 
week}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  solid at mornings and a week solid at afternoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Even when
 you were three you only did mornings or afternoons - when you weren't working part time or did you go a full day then when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 I didn't start work when I were twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 When you first started school did you do a full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh yes, you - you went to school }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 for full}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  days, yes, you had full days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 did nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  'til twelve and then you came home for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 And then you did an afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, there were no stopping to school dinners because we didn't have s
chool dinners in those days. You'd to come home but - being little like that - they'd all - somebody'd bring you home you know - a bigger girl'd bring you home because - me mother used to work and she used to come home at - meal time to be there with you 
to make your meal and then she'd go back to work afternoon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3100269\charrsid11677679 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Who took you in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Mother used to ask somebody - bigger to take us, you see, somebody that were a lot bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Were you near to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Very near to school, it was only end of the street and just over. It were no trouble - you were home in five to ten minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Do you remember what time afternoon school started and what time you finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well - two 'til four. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What did you think of school - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
No, I didn't because you see - it were this way. I didn't get a lot of schooling in the bit of time that I went because if ever me mother were ill we had to stay at home and - and - be able to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You mean when the babies were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
That's right. Ask and we'd be allowed to stay at home - so I missed a lot of schooling that way because - they had to rely on - on - on the children to help them in those days and I mean they weren't as keen - they were - they were keen
 to a certain extent but they weren't keen to fine you for things because you - you had to take a note and they knew it were true that - that you - you was at home for that purpose you see and you weren't by yourself because there were that many that - th
ey knew it were right you see. There were that many all in same boat sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh I - I respected them especially the one that had taught me father because she thought it were wonderful that she should 
teach me father and then she'd come to teach - she - she taught one, two - five of us, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What about the other teachers - did you like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They were very nice and they were very good to you. Especially if they - in any way that they coul
d help you sort of thing, they'd - they'd help you - they - they weren't strict and they weren't bullies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did they emphasise anything as important in life like manners or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 tidiness
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  or punctuality or ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well they were - there were v
arious teachers I mean - we didn't go to the same one each - you know - were various teachers and I mean - they were very - you know, they were very good and they were this way were the teachers, there weren't a lot of class distinction they used to make 
you all alike sort of thing. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They never singled anyone out for special treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Very - very - it were very, very - very, very few that they did. But - used to get very annoyed if they knew that you were a good scholar but in my case I was
n't a good scholar so I mean it didn't make any difference to me but if they found where there were a good scholar they would try to get them to school more than what - what they did you know if they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You don't remember anything being emphasised as very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
No, except - that - except I would like to get away from school to be honest. I'd rather work than go to school because I used to - I still do like housework - I like - you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They weren't keen on punctuality or tidiness or anything special like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Oh yes, you'd to go tidy because I mean - they were this way - they - you had to show your hands and you'd have to have clean shoes and I mean if you didn't you were out but that were something that were done at home. E
ven in the poor days you see - you saw kiddies going to school and could see their face - your face through the shoes. They were so - because their fathers and mothers had been brought up like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You never saw children without shoes in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well there were but I mean - there were - even in them days there were what were called Cinderella fund and they used to be sent down but that was some of the - my mother never faced - as ever going, she always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 She wouldn't let you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
No, because her independence were there you see, she was so independent were me mother and that's something I can be proud of as a child I were never sent to have shoes or pumps or anything in those days - they were always - me mother always saw we were
 all right because - before seek their aid she sought the aid of her own family and that's how it's been - always taught to us to keep together as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 In the school were there boys as well as girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh yes, it were a mixed school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen - how did they punish you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You were sent to headmaster and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Then what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You'd get six of the best on each hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes - girls go
t three on each hand and boys got six. And same as if you were late when bell had gone and everybody had marched in and you'd be late you'd to never go into your class, you'd to stand at the master's desk and for being late even if you - you'd a good excu
se and you'd had to do something, same as if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 anybody}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 were ill at home and you'd had to go to the doctors - in those days you'd to take a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 note}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 to doctor, there were no ringing up - and you - you took a note to doctor well many a time you'd to wait your turn 
to - to hand this note in and you were late. That were no excuse - you were late but you got three on each hand for being late and you had to have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What else were you punished for in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well I mean - well for all sorts of things like s
ame as talking and - you know - being late into your class into - you know - and they rang the bell to run to your lines and things like that but mostly - and for playing truant you - it were a right punishment. Oh yes, my brother once ran away and he got
 
best hiding - he couldn't sit down for a week. He got caned so many times on his backside that he couldn't sit down. And they came to see me - mother about it and me mother had to accept it although me mother didn't agree with punishment he got and that w
ere when my father were a soldier and me mother - absolutely played pot but - he'd to take his punishment because he'd played truant - he'd gone to see police bobbies, you know, the policemen march - drilling in Pell Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did your mother and father ta
ke an interest in your schoolwork - did they ever go to the school or see the teachers or ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well - it were very - me father knew them because he delivered coal at biggest part of the - of the houses you see because he were l
ocal coalman for district sort of ting and me father saw them and - but me mother - they'd never no cause to go see as regards going to school or - or anything that went off like. We just went because that were it - you'd school to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did all the children come from the same type of homes as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, more or less - more or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you have any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Were there any children left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, very rare. You were - you were all so
rt of - made alike and you sort of played with - and - and marched and - and were in school with the people that were all ready living round your own - you went - you were more or less all together every day sort of thing. The - year after year, month aft
er month, year after year you had more or less all together sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You never saw anybody left out of things at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Very - no, I never - I can never remember ever anybody being left out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 All the children were the same in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
I can never remember any work house children, I don't think there were a work house near us to be honest. No, if there were I didn't know about it as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No. No, none of us - not any of our family ever went to another school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How old were you when you left school - you were twelve weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Twelve, and I were thirteen when I actually left because I did - no I was fourteen when I left because if you went to work half time at tw
elve you had to go to school while you was fourteen. But if you left at thirteen to go - if you went - half - if you went half time - no - if you went to school and didn't go half time you were allowed to work full time at thirteen. My husband were one of
 
the ones that worked full time at thirteen but I did two years half days because me mother was so hard up for money that I went the half day but she regretted it because twelve months and I'd have been working full time but me sister didn't - me sister le
ft at thirteen you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, because I didn't like school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You didn't do any part time education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well I wish now th
at I'd have - you know - been more educated and had more schooling, I think the younger end now that - that have more schooling, same as me own daughter, I mean, she, you know, went to school and I mean - I think it's better. I think if we had have had mo
re schooling I think it'd have been better in - in after life 'cos we'd have had - got better jobs, we wouldn't have had to go in mill and things like that - we'd have been - you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 But you liked your work in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh yes, I liked me work in mill - they were happy days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Do you think you benefited from your days in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well I don't know - I - I - to be honest with you I didn't like school. I liked school when school bell had gone and you were coming home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 So you didn't really think you benefited}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3100269\charrsid11677679  much?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, I didn't because I didn't like school that much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You worked half time in school but you didn't do a part time job as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh no, you weren't allowed - just do your two half days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Mill. I went straight back to go full day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 And you were a spinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes. And then I - I graduated from that - from spinning to go through mill until I ended up being a reeler and a - and a wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What kind of mill was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 It was - it was a - spinning mill - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 A wool mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Yes. Yes. And the - you see, you could - sort of benefit yourself by your work and - and more you moved up and better jobs that you got - well I ended up as a reeler and a warper.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did you get your job in the first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Me mother made us go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You got it through }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 your mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, me mother was - me mother worked in the mill as a - in the drawing - the heavy drawing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What hours did you work - do you remember - when you went full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Sane. Half past six to five o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Sometimes it just depended. Some mills worked and some didn't you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You didn't do Sunday work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh no. No. And never overtime, we always went - went out when }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 whistle}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  blow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you work half day Saturday though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Was - one part - one period we did, we'd to work Saturday mornings and then it was knocked off and it were - you know - a lot of us - we
ll, the mills went short time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What were you paid - do you remember your wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 I do remember me wage - a pound and tenpence. Of all - not - I - when I first started I'd six and ten a week a
nd when I left - when I were - you know - growing up and into me teens I - I got up - when I actually left to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 I had a pound and tenpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh I thought it were a fortune. In fact some weeks we used to have twenty-three shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 When you first started did you think it was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well you had to do because I mean that was what the wages were, they were very poor were wages you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did you get on with the people you worked with in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh champion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did you feel about the work - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh it were lovely - yes, they were - they were good days were mill days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh - he were very nice because he - he'd had all the family. He'd had biggest part of the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did you feel about him though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 
Oh we liked him - he were - he were a - he were a good - boss to work for but - he didn't mix with you but you saw him and you could go with any problem to him like and he'd sort it out for you, you know.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You've always been in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Would you have preferred another type of occupation if you could have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What would you have liked to have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well I wanted to go - I always wanted }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 to work}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 in an hospital. Yes. Yes. And always wanted to go and that were my secret ambition and has been for years. And I've never - the only chance I've ever had to go into the hospital to work was when I lost my husb
and and then unfortunately I was too old but I could have found, you know, employment - I'd have loved to have worked in an hospital although I've had me share of hospitals - you know - having sickness such a lot but I'd have loved to have gone in there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you have to serve an apprenticeship in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
No, you'd to - just trained for the jobs and then you - you'd to sort of train for each job that you cold better yourself you know in them mills you could -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How long did you have to train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well it just depended on, you know, how quick you could pick it up sort of thing 'cos there were easy jobs and there were hard jobs. There were - and there were good jobs and there were bad jobs. You could - take your choice when you went in we chos
e to be that and then, you know, sort of - went from - you know - one little job to another until we bettered ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How do you mean you could choose when you went in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well you could - you went spinning or twisting or winding or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 reeling}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  or - you know - but, if you - our boss where we worked liked you to go in spinning and work your way up and you had to do and I left I was a reeler and a warper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Were you in a trade union in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes, we - we had a union then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 And you were in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
We had - yes, but it - it sort of fell through. There used to be a lot of trouble about things that went on. We used to pay a few coppers a week you know but it fell through, it - you know - they kept - having it on and having it off a
nd at finish it - well it - it were disbanded altogether like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you ever take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No. No. And it - they were never much trouble there in the mill you know - all - all the years I worked there and if it could find yo
u work although depression were on it share it equally amongst you that we - we had signing on days even then with bad days and good days like - we'd plenty, you know, of - upsetment sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you ever feel there was a division of interest amongst the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well it - you found interest in your work and your job like you know, you found interest this way, that you were dying to get that - that bit better every - every - every week sort of better yourself you know and get - go out for m
ore way you know. Always get that bit better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers - did you feel that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well there were with weavers. Oh yes, the weavers were very snooty. They
 were. Because they - they thought their job were - you know - was that essential they couldn't, you know, do without 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did they show it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh it - it were - obvious, I mean, if they were a weaver that were it - if they were a weaver you k
now you'd had it sort of thing. They thought - there again they thought they were a cut above you if they were a weaver because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They wouldn't talk to you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh no. And - and if you said you were going to walk through the we
aving well it were more than your place were worth - if you weren't a weaver you couldn't go through. Oh no. They were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They didn't dress special as the Lancashire weavers did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well - yes they - they all - well it - it could be different becaus
e the - you know they started dressing different from the ordinary mill hands - they used to call us mill hands but they were weavers, but they were all mill hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 They dressed better you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes. They were - weren't they. They were mill hand
s - they were just doing same job as us in the mill and it were a mill job, they were mill hands but they were that class distinction between you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Would you say that working full time changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 But - 
I don't know except - we'd happy - they were happy days and sort of you looked forward to your job you know. I - I used to like working in mill, I worked in mill right up to being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  and after I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 . Well - yes, but I mean - I knew that I had 
that job to do and I had to do it sort of thing whether I liked or not because I couldn't do anything else. You couldn't say, well I'll go to this, that or other because you hadn't chance - you hadn't chance - you'd to stay put.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you suddenly feel grown up though when you were working full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh I - yes, yes, but I mean, wages weren't big you know, no, they weren't big right through years weren't mill wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all? With your brothers or your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh no. Oh - all the same - we still are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you still go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 For a long time, yes, and then we got sort of that - we started - you know - looking round for a young man sort of thing that 
- but not - not daring to take him home because he wouldn't have been welcome, far from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Oh me mo - me father wouldn't have accepted anybody, not in us teens - he'd have seen them off merrily would me father. He would - you daren't - you daren't ask to stay out late and go to pictures late, well that were a crime and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did you spend your spare time then after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh you'd to - me father and mother were very strict for a long time and to go to a dance well that
 was - you'd never dare ask - it were my brother who took us to our first dance and he had to nearly beg for a week and me father - before me father softened and - there were no good come of dancing, you know, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Why?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No I don't know but tha
t was his view you see, he'd never been and - and he stuck to that and sort of it grew with him like you know, anyway at finish he accepted it and started letting us go out but we'd to be - I'd be seventeen or eighteen before me father sort of }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 softened}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  lik
e, you know, before he - you could stay out - never allowed you to stay out late. Not even when I were courting I had to be in at half past nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did he want to know where you'd gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh - so long as you're in at half past nine that were all that mattered because we were all in bed at ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did your parents like to meet your friends when you were getting older - did you bring them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well we did, yes, but - you know - when - when you were courting that were another matter. My
 father told my hus - well, he were me young man at that time - our bed times ten o'clock and it was sort of like it or lump it. He said to me I can take the hint and half past nine he used to say, it's our bedtime, and that were it. My - me - my husband 
daren't keep me about because me father'd have brought house down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 When you did go out in the evening who did you go out with before you met your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Oh mostly with me sister and with a few boyfriends like on quiet sort of - what - you know,
 we used to - well never afford to go to pictures 'cos we never had a lot to go with but we used to - talk to them and - you know - we - we found a way round it somehow or other you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 But you didn't go dancing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 
Well it were mostly to a - you know - friends house where they'd a piano and there's a bit of music going but it were always that looking at time - looking at - you know - watching your watch sort of thing all the time and - racing home and - you know -
 but me sister - me sisters got that we thought well - you know - we're going to show me dad that we'll - you know - be a bit later.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 How did you meet your boyfriends then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12155485\charrsid11677679 Oh - well - more or less we - we had a few like before we sort of settled
 down but it were - with you know, promenading in the park at Sunday or - yes, and - and meeting them that way or - you know - getting to know - through your friends like if you went to a party or anything, but even so you - if you told me father you were
 going to a party - party - what sort of a party? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You know, and he - you'd that much explaining to do anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 What kind of parties were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Well it'd be - you know - the - they'd concoct something up in mill that we'd - we - we'd have some - yo
u know - some parties or others we'd see that we got asked because nearly everybody were same - they'd all to be in early. It were a crime if you were out late. My - even my - my husband when he were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  to me were twenty-five and he had to be in at te
n o'clock and he were twenty-five years of age and he were never allowed to smoke a cigarette. His own father and I mean there - look at - his father was stricter than mine. But - in those days your mother and father ruled with iron hand sort of thing - y
ou'd to do as you were told Discipline came before everything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Did you ever take an interest in politics yourself as you were growing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No, but me - my husband were - my husband did because - he - he were - if he'd have had his health he'd
 have liked to have, you know, gone into be a Labour - he were a right Labour man you know and he -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Even when he was a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes. Even when I were first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  to him he were right interested in Labour movement you know but never - he never had his health to follow it up but he always voted Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 But you never took an interest at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
No, I used to listen to him you know and he used to - he used to say to me, you know, I used to say to him thought - you're votes your own private aff
air - you've a right to please yourself. He says, but I hope you'll always vote Labour. He were right true Labour man right up to dying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 If anybody did anything wrong in the district where you lived in Bradford did the neighbours have any special way 
of showing that they disapproved - do you ever remember anything like that - do you ever remember them making effigies of anyone or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No. No, they were - in fact the people right through the years and - were always the same, the same as when anybody were getting }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 it were a - it were right - right jubilee you know - it were - and everything that went - the same as when war were over it - it - it were right grand - everybody got together and - and I don't think all our street co
uld have raised two shillings but - you know - it were right grand you know - it - I was saying, it were always a friendly sort of atmosphere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You never knew anybody do anything wrong and the neighbours be upset?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 No. I mean - well, if anybody th
ere - it was very, very rare, they - they - there were any arguments or any bullying or fight - you never saw much of that. It were more or less all - well, we all seemed to grow up together and - and just be the same as we are today, you know. It - I don
'
t think - I'd - to tell you the truth I don't think there were many round by us that - that did that because - in our teens we were all this way, we were all you know, hoping to better one another you know, have a wedding and it be right nice affair and t
hings like that but - I don't - I don't think there were anybody round by us that - there were anything like that, I mean when I were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
 I sort of left it behind as I'd always known it sort of thing. Yes, where I lived. But it isn't there anymore - it'
s come down under the slum clearance, you know, the - rebuilding the - well they're making a lot of flat. But going home now isn't the same to me you know. Homes gone. The - the magic's gone out of the place altogether. Going home isn't going home, that's
 gone - even when I - pass me mother's and father's house that's standing it - it's not the same you know, not like it were when me mother and dad had it. They left there where I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13986236 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679  from and went to a bigger house up on the main road up on the righ
t side and it were a lovely house because the family that was left were getting better jobs and you know, growing up and me mother moved, you know, and it were right nice but even there house has lost its magic - when I pass it - it isn't me mother's anym
ore you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 You always remember your home with magic do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Yes, when I think of home I always think of it as it was but now it's gone you know when you go under this new scheme you know it's all - all the beauty's gone out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 So the poverty really didn't matter, you still think of your home as magic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 That's right, yes. And I still think - I think of my young days as happy days really. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Looking back at life you feel that they were happy days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Yes. Yes, because we - we made our own happiness out of nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8336051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 Looking back what did you feel about the poverty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15404701 EY  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14909196\charrsid11677679 
Well I - looking back at it now you don't think of it as being poverty you know, sort of - it was poverty in a way but - there were that - there were t
